dcterms:creator: P. Cunningham
D. Doyle
J. Loughrey
dcterms:description: The Moodle Dataset is constructed from records of student footprints on the Moodle Virtual Learning Environment (VLE) for a single class delivered within Robert Gordon University, UK. It captures vital touchpoints that can be used as proxy measures of student engagement, consisting of 74 students enrolled in a Computer Science class during Semester 1 of 2020/2021.
dcterms:title: Moodle Dataset

dcterms:creator: S. Wachter
B. Mittelstadt
C. Russell
dcterms:description: The Loan-2015 dataset is a subset of the Lending Club loan dataset from 2015, containing records used to predict if a loan will be paid in full or not. It consists of 421,095 data instances with 151 features, focusing on binary classification for loan acceptance.
dcterms:title: Loan-2015 Dataset

dcterms:creator: P. Cunningham
D. Doyle
J. Loughrey
dcterms:description: The Alcohol Dataset consists of 127,800 data instances with 7 features, including gender and meal consumption, used to predict if the Blood Alcohol Concentration (BAC) is over a regulatory limit. It is a binary classification task.
dcterms:title: Alcohol Dataset

dcterms:creator: S. Wachter
B. Mittelstadt
C. Russell
dcterms:description: The Income Dataset contains 45,222 data instances based on the US 1994 Census database, with 15 features used to predict yearly income in US Dollars. The task is to classify whether income is above or below 50k per year.
dcterms:title: Income Dataset

dcterms:description: The Credit Dataset is a credit card application approval dataset with 653 data instances and 15 anonymised features describing an applicant. The task is to predict if the credit card application was approved or not.
dcterms:title: Credit Dataset
